The paper deals with the complexity of modal satisfiability for certain combinations of modal logics, which is a topic that falls under the area of computational logic. The use of negation normal form and the restriction to one propositional variable suggest a focus on complexity theory and algorithmic analysis, which are common themes in the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The investigation of interdependencies among logics and the characterization of the diamond-free, 1-variable fragments of multimodal logics suggest a focus on formal methods and theoretical computer science, which are also relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-categories.
